description:
After we updated Virtuoso from v7.2.1 to v7.2.4.2,
the CPU load became to go up to 100% when we run its look up processing via SPARQL.
With Virtuoso v7.2.4.2, the CPU load goes up to 100% during the look up processing is running,
and it takes 3 times longer than v7.2.1.
The number of stored data is 2000.
The spec of server is as follows:

CPU: Intel Xeon X5670 2.93GHz
RAM: 7.5GB

It is really appreciated if you kindly give us advice regarding the suspected root causes
and the way to avoid this issue.
The following is our query to run SPARQL look up processing.
sparql
prefix odp: <http://www.example.com/LOD/ns#>
prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
prefix dc: <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/>
prefix dct: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/>
prefix schema: <http://schema.org/>
select ?s ?label ?url ?locality ?description ?categoryURI ?facilityURI ?outdoor ?charge ?reservation
 ?ageFrom ?ageTo ?location ?promoter ?listImage ?detailImage ?date1 ?time1 ?date2 ?time2 ?created ?modified
  from <http://www.example.com/LOD/spot>
  from <http://www.example.com/LOD/place>
 where {
  ?s a odp:Spot ;
    odp:spot-type <http://www.example.com/LOD/sp/type/2> ;
    rdfs:label ?label ;
    odp:spot-category ?categoryURI ;
    odp:locality ?locality ;
    odp:location ?location ;
    dct:created ?created ;
    dct:modified ?modified ;
    odp:outdoor ?outdoor ;
    odp:charge ?charge ;
    odp:reservation ?reservation ;
    odp:age/odp:fromAge ?ageFrom ;
    odp:age/odp:toAge ?ageTo .
    OPTIONAL {
      ?s schema:url ?url .
    }
    OPTIONAL {
      ?s odp:listImage ?listImage .
    }
    OPTIONAL {
      ?s odp:detailImage ?detailImage .
    }
    OPTIONAL {
      ?s odp:openDate1 ?date1 .
    }
    OPTIONAL {
      ?s odp:openTime1 ?time1 .
    }
    OPTIONAL {
      ?s odp:openDate2 ?date2 .
    }
    OPTIONAL {
      ?s odp:openTime2 ?time2 .
    }
    OPTIONAL {
      ?s odp:promoter ?promoter .
    }
    OPTIONAL {
      ?s odp:facility ?facilityURI .
      ?location odp:facility ?facilityURI .
    }
    OPTIONAL {
      ?s dc:description ?description .
    }
}
